              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STANK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A EJ309 scintillator detector was used for the",
                "detection of the neutron energy spectrum at the",
                "sample position using unfolding method."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A twin grid ionization chamber (GIC) was used",
                "as the charged particle detector. The distance from",
                "the cathode to the grid was 6.1 cm. The working gas",
                "of the GIC was Ar + CH4 (10%) with the pressure of",
                "1.1 bar for both experiments. The high voltages",
                "applied on the cathode and anodes were -1200 V and",
                "+600 V and the grid electrodes were grounded for all",
                "measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 232Th(OH)4 sample and a 238U3O8 sample were",
                "prepared each on a tantalum foil 0.10 mm in thickness.",
                "For 232Th(OH)4, isotopic enrichment was about 100%,",
                "diameter was 44.0 mm, thickness was 601.9 ug/cm2, and",
                "number of nuclei was 1.837E19.",
                "For 238U3O8, isotopic enrichment was 99.999%,",
                "diameter was 43.0 mm, thickness was 600.8 ug/cm2, and",
                "number of nuclei was 1.872E19."
              ]
            }
